  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "1Jzb6yzQzSiE9zLr8ohkrdEFV34=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# input types should reflect user intent with simple specific fields\n\nOperation input types should be designed around user intent:\n\n```graphql\n// \u2705 Simple, specific \u2014 reflects what the user provides\ninput AddLineItemInput {\n    id: OID!\n    description: String!\n    quantity: Int!\n    unitPrice: Amount_Money!\n}\n\n// \u274c Complex nested structure \u2014 harder to use and validate\ninput AddLineItemInput {\n    item: LineItemInput!\n    metadata: MetadataInput\n    options: OptionsInput\n}\n```\n\nKeep inputs flat and focused. The system auto-generates `OID` for new objects \u2014 callers provide IDs through the input schema because [[reducer purity requires all dynamic values from action input]].\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
    }
  },
